<h2>Sedition Acts</h2>
<p>Finally, the Sedition Act stirred the most outcry. The law criminalized "false, scandalous, and malicious writing" against the government. It targeted criticism and dissent, effectively undermining the First Amendment's protections of free speech and press.</p>
